4 has to be (1, 2, 3, 4) - col_or_row = {1, 2, 3, 4}
3 has to be (1, 2, 4, 3), (1, 3, 4, 2), (2, 3, 4, 1), (2, 3, 1, 4) or (2, 1, 3, 4) - for nums in col_or_row, exactly one (col_or_row[i] < col_or_row[i-1]) must be true
2 has to be (1, 4, 2, 3), (1, 4, 3, 2), (2, 1, 4, 3), (2, 4, 1, 3), (2, 4, 3, 1), (3, 4, 1, 2), (3, 4, 2, 1), (3, 1, 4, 2), (3, 2, 4, 1), (3, 1, 2, 4) or (3, 2, 1, 4) - for nums in col_or_row, exactly one (col_or_row[i] < col_or_row[i-1] && col_or_row[i+1] < col_or_row[i-1]) must be true
1 has to be (4, 1, 2, 3), (4, 1, 3, 2), (4, 2, 1, 3), (4, 2, 3, 1), (4, 3, 1, 2) or (4, 3, 2, 1) - col_or_row[0] = 4